  <span id="freeText5961750211460314043" style="display:none">Ghosts can’t seem to keep their opinions to themselves.<br /><br />Seventeen-year-old Nate Shaw should know; he’s been talking to them since he was twelve. But they aren’t the only ones making his high school years a living hell. All Nate wants is to keep his secret and keep his head down until he can graduate. That is, until the new boy, James Powell, takes a seat next to him in homeroom. James not only notices him, he manages to work his way into Nate’s life. But James has issues of his own.<br /><br />Between dead grandmothers and living aunts, Nate has to navigate the fact that he’s falling in love with his only friend, all while getting advice from the most unusual places.<br /><br />Ghosts, bullies, first love: it’s a lot to deal with when you’re just trying to survive senior year.</span>
