<div id="review_2040999607" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2040999607" />
    <a title="Mónica BQ" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/27512341-m-nica-bq"><img alt="Mónica BQ" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1443248718p2/27512341.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2040999607?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mónica BQ" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mónica BQ" href="/user/show/27512341-m-nica-bq">Mónica BQ</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/34607494-a-boy-worth-knowing">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2040999607" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5078214471591806385">I did not expect to like this book as much as I ended up doing.<br/><br/>Although the story stalled a tiny bit in the middle with an unnecessarily long back and forth, the rest of it was quite good.<br/><br/><b>This book was cute, and fun, and a bit cheesy and quintessential YA. And I adored the whole of it. Which surprised the hell out of me. Also: great Bi rep.</b><br/><br/>Nate is an amazing character with a quirky side to his personality that made the whole book thoroughly enjoyable. James is the perfect YA boyfriend, but in a </span>
  <span id="freeText5078214471591806385" style="display:none">I did not expect to like this book as much as I ended up doing.<br /><br />Although the story stalled a tiny bit in the middle with an unnecessarily long back and forth, the rest of it was quite good.<br /><br /><b>This book was cute, and fun, and a bit cheesy and quintessential YA. And I adored the whole of it. Which surprised the hell out of me. Also: great Bi rep.</b><br /><br />Nate is an amazing character with a quirky side to his personality that made the whole book thoroughly enjoyable. James is the perfect YA boyfriend, but in a <i>good</i> way. He's flawed, he's grieving, he has his own life happenings and yet he is a great teen, slowly falling in love with the main character. It was honestly all sweet as fuck. And it was just what I needed.<br /><br />Plus, the writing was fantastic, which kept me engrossed with the story and I finished the book in a day. <b>Also, major kudos for having great adult women in the story. Finding characters like Aunt Susan and Nana in what's basically m/m YA Contemporary Romance was such a breath of fresh air that it lifted my spirits just by knowing that there's authors out there able to write women like these.</b><br /><br />I only have one minor complaint: <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I felt a tad uneasy at the approach the author had as for the reasons Penny had for hating on Nate so much. To use what basically amounts to the teen version of "women hysterics" for the all the bulling Nate went through just because she was turned down in middle grade by her gay best friend felt kind of icky. It ruined what had been a 5 star read up until then. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.<br /><br />I can't wait to read more from Cosgrove and I really hope more people get this novel. It has very few ratings and reviews in GR for such a fantastic book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5078214471591806385" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


